<recipeml version="0.5">
  <recipe>
    <head>
      <title>Apple Cinnamon Pudding</title>
      <categories>
        <cat>Desserts</cat>
        <cat>Vegan</cat></categories>
      <yield>1</yield></head>
    <ingredients>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>2</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Apple juice</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>cup</unit></amt>
        <item>Water</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>pinch</unit></amt>
        <item>Sea salt (optional)</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>cup</unit></amt>
        <item>AM Rice and Shine</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>teaspoon</unit></amt>
        <item>Cinnamon</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>cup</unit></amt>
        <item>Roasted pecan or other nuts (chopped)</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>teaspoon</unit></amt>
        <item>Vanilla</item></ing></ingredients>
    <directions>
      <step>  Bring juice, water and salt to a boil in a large saucepan.  Stir in Rice
  and Shine and cinnamon.  Turn heat to low.  Simmer 5 minutes.  Remove from
  heat.  Stir in nuts and vanilla.  Let set until slightly cool.  Pour into
  a 9" square pan.  Refrigerate until set and cool.  Serve squares plain or
  with a little fruit syrup.
  
